<header role="banner">
  <h1><a href="/" style="color: #f0f6fc; text-decoration: none;"><span class="accent">727a8</span>.com</a></h1>
  <p class="subtitle">When Can I File <a href="https://whatischapter7.com/" title="Chapter 7">Chapter 7</a> Again?</p>
</header>
<nav class="breadcrumb-nav" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="https://727a8.com/">Home</a><span class="separator">&rsaquo;</span><span>Date Calculator</span></nav>


<article id="main" role="main">

<h2>Chapter 7 Refiling Date Calculator</h2>

<p>Enter your prior bankruptcy filing date and case type below. This calculator will tell you the earliest date you can file a new <a href="https://whatischapter7.com/" title="Chapter 7">Chapter 7</a> and receive a <a href="https://bankruptcydischarge.org/" title="discharge">discharge</a>, based on Sections <a href="/">727(a)(8)</a> and <a href="/727a9.html">727(a)(9)</a> of the Bankruptcy Code.</p>

<div class="calc-box">
  <div class="field-group">
    <label for="priorType">What chapter was your prior case?</label>
    <select id="priorType" aria-describedby="priorTypeHelp">
      <option value="7">Chapter 7</option>
      <option value="11"><a href="https://section1191.org/" title="Chapter 11">Chapter 11</a> (individual)</option>
      <option value="13"><a href="https://chapter7vs13.org/" title="Chapter 13">Chapter 13</a></option>
      <option value="12">Chapter 12</option>
    </select>
    <div id="priorTypeHelp" style="color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: -0.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Select the chapter of your <em>prior</em> case that resulted in a <a href="https://bankruptcydischarge.org/" title="discharge">discharge</a>.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="field-group">
    <label for="filingDate">Prior case filing date (petition date)</label>
    <input type="date" id="filingDate" aria-describedby="filingDateHelp">
    <div id="filingDateHelp" style="color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: -0.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">This is the date you <em>filed</em> the prior case, not the date you received the discharge.</div>
  </div>

  <div id="seventyPctGroup">
    <label style="font-weight: normal; font-size: 0.9rem;">
      <input type="checkbox" id="seventyPct" style="margin-right: 0.5rem; width: auto;">
      I paid at least 70% of unsecured claims and the plan was proposed in <a href="https://chapter13plan.org/" title="good faith">good faith</a> with best effort.
    </label>
    <div style="color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 0.5rem;">If checked, the 727(a)(9) 6-year bar may not apply. See <a href="/727a9.html">Section 727(a)(9)</a> for details.</div>
  </div>

  <button class="calc-btn" onclick="calculate()" aria-label="Calculate eligibility date">Calculate Eligibility Date</button>

  <div id="result" role="status" aria-live="polite"></div>
</div>

<h2>How This Calculator Works</h2>

<p>The calculator applies the following rules from the Bankruptcy Code:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Prior Chapter 7 or 11 discharge:</strong> You must wait <strong>8 years</strong> from the prior filing date to file a new Chapter 7 and receive a discharge. This is <a href="/">Section 727(a)(8)</a>.</li>
  <li><strong>Prior <a href="https://chapter7vs13.org/" title="Chapter 13">Chapter 13</a> discharge:</strong> You must wait <strong>6 years</strong> from the prior filing date - unless you paid 100% of unsecured claims, or paid at least 70% in <a href="https://chapter13plan.org/" title="good faith">good faith</a> with best effort. This is <a href="/727a9.html">Section 727(a)(9)</a>.</li>
  <li><strong>Prior Chapter 12 discharge:</strong> Same 6-year rule as Chapter 13, with the same exceptions. Also <a href="https://727a8.com" title="Section 727 Chapter 7 Discharge - Open Bankruptcy Project" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Section 727</a>(a)(9).</li>
</ul>

<p>All periods are measured from <strong>filing date to filing date</strong>. The discharge date of the prior case does not affect the calculation.</p>

<h2>What About Filing Chapter 13 Instead?</h2>

<p>This calculator only addresses Chapter 7 eligibility. If you want to file Chapter 13 instead, different rules apply under <a href="/vs-1328f.html">Section 1328(f)</a>:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Prior Chapter 7 discharge: 4-year bar on Chapter 13 discharge (filing date to filing date)</li>
  <li>Prior Chapter 13 discharge: 2-year bar on Chapter 13 discharge (filing date to filing date)</li>
</ul>

<p>Use the <a href="https://1328f.com/check.html">1328f.com eligibility screener</a> to check all discharge bars across all chapter combinations at once.</p>

<div class="callout yellow">
<h4>Not Legal Advice</h4>
<p>This calculator provides general information based on the Bankruptcy Code. Individual circumstances may vary. Court practices, local rules, and specific case facts can affect eligibility. Consult a bankruptcy attorney before making filing decisions.</p>
</div>

</article>

